## Limitations

The findings are based on existing literature and may not account for all individual variations in pain perception. Additionally, much of the research relies on self-reported data, which can be subjective. Further studies, particularly those incorporating diverse populations and advanced imaging techniques, are needed to deepen the understanding of gender differences in pain perception.

